pull_request.title: Add ERC721 precompile information
pull_request.body:
## Summary
Not able to do from a contract. Ideally IERC721(address).transferFrom should be same as deploying a contract 'At address'

May be need to set some config file on CENNZnet node side to achieve the above thing. Right now at least call to transferFrom and approve can be done if we create a contract at some NFT address derived.

Next thing would be, I will check with ether-js lib, if we can do this in a smart contract.

issue.title: Issue with doing transaction for ERC721 precompile.

comment.body: I can also explain the flow in code.. 1. It goes from [runner.rs](https://github.com/cennznet/cennznet/blob/729105168699dd497b072c4d2a08f883be2af3a7/runtime/src/runner.rs#L139) call 2 Gets to this library cargo/git/checkouts/evm-31951a45719dc0d6/52d5fe5/src/executor/stack/executor.rs `#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)] fn call_inner( &mut self, code_address: H160, transfer: Option, input: Vec, target_gas: Option, is_static: bool, take_l64: bool, take_stipend: bool, context: Context, ) -> Capture<(ExitReason` The main line of interest in this function is `let mut runtime = Runtime::new(Rc::new(code), Rc::new(input), context, self.config); let reason = self.execute(&mut runtime); ` which internally tries to find opcode, I expect it to resolve with opcode /// `CALL` pub const CALL: Opcode = Opcode(0xf1); ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29415595/185261817-53e23053-be3c-45cd-a5bc-7997b503cf03.png) However it fails to get the right opcode and the routing_prefix does not matches the address of nft which is 0xaAAAaaAA00000000000000000000000000000000

issue.title: Issue with doing transaction for ERC721 precompile.
ERC721 precompile owner_of to return evm address over CENNZnet address
issue.body:
Return type for owner_of for erc721 is a Ethereum address.

https://github.com/cennznet/cennznet/blob/develop/evm-precompiles/erc721/src/lib.rs#L190
https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/api/token/erc721#IERC721-ownerOf-uint256-

On using custom interface to return me a string
 `function ownerOf(uint256 tokenId) external view returns (string memory);`

It gets me JSON-RPC error

`call to Test.ownerOfProxy
call to Test.ownerOfProxy errored: Internal JSON-RPC error.
{
  "code": -32603,
  "message": "VM Exception while processing transaction: revert",
  "data": ""
}`
